[
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ Bass music playing ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "Nishant Nelogal: Hello, and welcome to WWDC.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=6"
  },
  {
    "text": "My name is Nishant, and I’m an engineer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the AVFoundation team.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, we will be looking at HLS Variants.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=14"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we will look at how you can inspect HLS variants, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "using AVFoundation APIs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "and later on, we will see how we can use the HLS variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=23"
  },
  {
    "text": "with downloads.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=26"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's start with variant inspection.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "You all must be familiar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "with what a typical master playlist looks like.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is an example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=36"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this particular playlist, we have two variants.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "One of the variants is an SDR variant with stereo audio, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the other one is a Dolby Vision variant ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=47"
  },
  {
    "text": "with Dolby Atmos audio.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "The asset representing this particular playlist ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=52"
  },
  {
    "text": "may be presented something like this in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "Looking closely, you see that the asset has 4K, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=58"
  },
  {
    "text": "Dolby Vision, and Dolby Atmos badges.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=62"
  },
  {
    "text": "Earlier, you had to get such information out of the band.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=66"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now in iOS 15, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can directly inspect the HLS playlist to infer them.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "For that, you start with an AVURLAsset ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=77"
  },
  {
    "text": "pointing to the location of your master playlist.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "Later on, you can obtain the HLS playlist ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "via the variant's property.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "This AVAssetVariant, as we see here, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "represents an HLS variant as is from the master playlist.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "So it has multiple properties ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "representing different media attributes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "Some of the attributes, such as the media bitrate, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be accessed directly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=104"
  },
  {
    "text": "Other attributes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as those related to video and audio renditions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "are grouped together in their own subclasses.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "They are called as VideoAttributes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "and AudioAttributes, respectively.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you see, each of them has relevant properties, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=120"
  },
  {
    "text": "which you can use to understand your asset.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now you know how to inspect HLS variants in AVFoundation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's see how we can use them with downloads.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=131"
  },
  {
    "text": "Downloading HLS content for offline playback ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "has been supported since 2016.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you're not familiar with HLS download APIs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=139"
  },
  {
    "text": "I would suggest you check out our earlier talk on the topic ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "from WWDC 2020.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "In iOS 15, we are taking our HLS download APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "and making them even more powerful.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "Typically, you would like to influence the HLS variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "selected for the download.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "This may be due to business requirements, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you just want to provide more choice to your users.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=162"
  },
  {
    "text": "Before, you could provide such input ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=165"
  },
  {
    "text": "via downloadTask options.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "We had an option for HDR, an option for lossless audio, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "and a few other attributes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "In iOS 15, we are expanding the variant selection ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the use of NSPredicates.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "You may be already familiar with using predicates from Core Data.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=183"
  },
  {
    "text": "If not, don’t worry, you will learn about them today.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "So to get started, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "let me introduce the variant qualifier interface.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "This interface allows you to specify your variant preferences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "to AVFoundation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "And, as I said, they can be constructed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "using NSPredicates.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let’s understand by looking at few examples.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=207"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here, we have a NSPredicate which expresses peak bitrate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be less than five megabits.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "You use this to construct your variant qualifier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "which instructs AVFoundation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=220"
  },
  {
    "text": "to prefer variants under five megabits.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "Simple enough, right? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let’s take a look at another example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here we create an NSPredicate for HDR video range.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "And similarly as before, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=233"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can construct a variant qualifier for it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=235"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also combine multiple predicates ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "to create a compound predicate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "and use them to create your variant qualifier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "Any property on variant can be used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "to create a predicate against.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "For properties such as audio channel count, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=251"
  },
  {
    "text": "which cannot be easily expressed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "using the predicate format string, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "we have custom constructors.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can look them up in our header doc ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "for variant qualifier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=261"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you have your variant qualifier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=264"
  },
  {
    "text": "you use it to create something called as content configuration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=266"
  },
  {
    "text": "Each content configuration represents a set of video, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=270"
  },
  {
    "text": "audio, and subtitle renditions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=274"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, let's understand with an example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=277"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is the variant qualifier ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=282"
  },
  {
    "text": "which combines the two predicates we saw earlier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "Eh, this is compounding. Ha-ha.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=287"
  },
  {
    "text": "It informs AVFoundation to prefer HDR variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "under five megabits.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also have a set of media selections ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "representing English and French audio, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "and English subtitle renditions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "Both of these can be used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "to create a content configuration object.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can create multiple of these content configurations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "and provide it to the downloadTask.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "These multiple content configurations are tied together ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the download configuration interface.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=317"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is the root which holds everything together.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=319"
  },
  {
    "text": "It is created with an AVURLAsset and needs an asset name, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "and optionally, an image.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=328"
  },
  {
    "text": "The asset name and image are displayed in the Settings app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "This allows your users to manage all of their downloads ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "in one place in the Settings app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=338"
  },
  {
    "text": "And of course, the downloadTask can be configured ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "with multiple content configurations.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "Looking closely, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=346"
  },
  {
    "text": "one of the content configurations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be designated as primary and the rest will be auxiliary.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "The difference between the two is ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "you typically want to download a primary set of video, audio, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=359"
  },
  {
    "text": "and subtitle renditions and then complement them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "with additional audio or subtitle renditions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=366"
  },
  {
    "text": "By specifying your additional renditions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=370"
  },
  {
    "text": "as auxiliary content configurations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "you instruct AVFoundation to optimize ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=375"
  },
  {
    "text": "and avoid downloading multiple video renditions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=377"
  },
  {
    "text": "It becomes more clear as we go over an example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is the complete example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we start by creating a download configuration ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "with AVURLAsset and a title.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "The primary content configuration ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=395"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the same one we saw earlier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=397"
  },
  {
    "text": "It is configured to download HDR variants under five megabits, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "with English and French audio and English subtitle renditions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this particular example, we would like to complement it ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "with an auxiliary content configuration ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=410"
  },
  {
    "text": "to download English audio in lossless format.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now we have both our content configurations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "which we want to download.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=418"
  },
  {
    "text": "Make sure to set ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "optimizesAuxiliary ContentConfigurations to true.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=422"
  },
  {
    "text": "By the way, it is true by default, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=426"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it allows AVFoundation to choose lossless variant, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "such that the lossless variant’s video rendition ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the same as the primary content configuration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=436"
  },
  {
    "text": "Setting it to false may cause lossless variant ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=439"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be evaluated independently, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=442"
  },
  {
    "text": "which may cause duplicate video renditions to be downloaded.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "This may increase your download size, which we don’t want.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=448"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, once you have the download configuration, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=452"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can use it to create the downloadTask.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=456"
  },
  {
    "text": "You resume the downloadTask to start the download.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "Starting in iOS 15, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can also observe the progress of the downloadTask ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "using NSProgress interface.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=466"
  },
  {
    "text": "The NSProgress object is KVO-observable, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=468"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you can use it to update your user interface.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "Moving on.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "We understand that some of you may have business logic ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "for selecting variants, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=479"
  },
  {
    "text": "which may be harder to express via predicates.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "For such cases, you can also choose ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "to choose the variants you want to download explicitly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=487"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here in this example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "we have already picked our primary and auxiliary variant ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=492"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the media selections to go with it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=495"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can instruct AVFoundation to download them as is, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "by creating a qualifier with the variant directly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "Be careful to select variants so that they are playable ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the device where they are downloaded.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's all we have today, folks.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "To wrap up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=512"
  },
  {
    "text": "we looked at how you can inspect HLS variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=513"
  },
  {
    "text": "and use them to configure the downloadTask.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=516"
  },
  {
    "text": "Along the way, we encountered different interfaces ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "for downloadTask configuration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first one was variant qualifier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is used to express your variant preferences.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=526"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we saw content configuration interface.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=529"
  },
  {
    "text": "The content configuration ties together ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=532"
  },
  {
    "text": "your variant preferences and your media selection choices.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=534"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, we saw the download configuration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=538"
  },
  {
    "text": "The download configuration is the root interface ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "which ties everything together.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=543"
  },
  {
    "text": "Last, but not the least, we also learned that ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=546"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can monitor your downloadTask using NSProgress.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=548"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information, check our header docs.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=552"
  },
  {
    "text": "They're very well commented.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=555"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you for watching and bye-bye! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10143/?time=559"
  }
]